<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">The Super Bowl is more than just a game — it's an experience. From the energy of the crowd to the halftime show, and of course the merch, every element plays a role in making the event unforgettable. The future of stadium shopping is changing just as fast as the game itself.</p>

<h2>Super Bowl LIX: the biggest game of the year</h2>
<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">Super Bowl LIX is set for February 9, 2025, at the Caesars Superdome in New Orleans, Louisiana, with the Kansas City Chiefs facing off against the Philadelphia Eagles in a championship rematch. With millions tuning in worldwide and thousands attending in person, the demand for fast, seamless experiences — both on and off the field — has never been higher.</p>

<h2>Faster checkouts, happier fans</h2>
<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">Teamwork Commerce has partnered with EXO to bring RFID-powered self-checkout to large-scale events, so fans spend less time in line and more time enjoying the action. Stadiums and arenas hosting major sporting events need technology that can handle peak crowd surges — traditional checkout creates bottlenecks that lead to frustration and lost sales. With EXO's RFID self-checkout technology, fans can grab merchandise, scan an entire basket instantly, and complete a purchase in under 32 seconds — three times faster than barcode scanning.</p>

<h2>Proven at NFL and MLB stadiums</h2>
<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">Teamwork Commerce and EXO have collaborated to enhance the retail experience at NFL and MLB stadiums, as well as major industry events like NRF. By combining Teamwork Commerce's point-of-sale solutions with EXO's self-checkout technology, stadiums can maximize efficiency, increase revenue, and improve fan satisfaction — retail teams get streamlined operations, and customers get a frictionless checkout.</p>

<h2>The future of stadium retail</h2>
<p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">As retail technology keeps evolving, expect more stadiums to adopt self-checkout to keep pace with modern fan expectations. As RFID tagging becomes more widespread, fast and seamless transactions will become the standard rather than the exception — so whether it's the Super Bowl, an NFL or MLB game, or a major retail event, an EXO and Teamwork Commerce integration may already be behind the counter.</p>
